\taxon{Lemma}
\title{Sum of independent [Poisson distributions](SP-000I)}

\p{
  Let #{ X_1 \sim  \text{Poi}(\lambda _1)  } and #{ X_2 \sim  \text{Poi}(\lambda _2)  } be independent random variables. Then #{ X_1 + X_2 \sim  \text{Poi}(\lambda _1 + \lambda _2)  }
}

\p{
  The proof is simply by calculating the [p.g.f](SP-000W)
}